bilal.onlinecourses.algorithmpt1.prog.assignment2

Class Deque<Item>

  • java.lang.Object
    • bilal.onlinecourses.algorithmpt1.prog.assignment2.Deque<Item>
  • Type Parameters:
    Item - the generic type of an item in this bag
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<Item>

    public class Deque<Item>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<Item>
    Created by Bilal on 2/18/2016. The Dequeue class is a generalization of a stack and a queue that supports adding and removing items from either the front or the back of the data structure. It supports addFirst, addLast, removeFirst and removeLast operations and iterating through the items in FIFO order.

    This implementation uses a doubly-linked list with a static nested class for linked-list nodes. The addFirst, addLast, removeFirst, removeLast, size, and is-empty operations all take constant time in the worst case.

    Author:
    Bilal Abdullah
